                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Choate</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram in cipher.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-01-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>[Mr. Choate suggests that if it is concluded to offer seized goods to sell both
                    consignor and consignee unite in sale where title is doubtful between them, this
                    course being preferable to incurring questions and delays in prize court,
                    although possibly causing delay in payment while getting consent from
                    consignee.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
